  "title": "Website: long delays before instantsearch works",
  "body": "I'm implementing instantsearch.js in vanilla JavaScript in a way very similar to the e-commerce (2nd) example in https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v1/examples/\r\n\r\nWhen it works, it works brilliantly. But often when I click in the search bar nothing happens. I must reload the page a few times and wait. Usually then somehow instantsearch begins to work.\r\n\r\nI thought maybe it was a promise issue so I implemented that (see code below). This seems to have no effect however.\r\n```\r\n            window.onload = function() {\r\n                let loadSearchPromise = search.start();\r\n                document.getElementById('search__input').onclick = function() {\r\n                    loadSearchPromise.then(() => {\r\n                      document.getElementById('show-result').style.display = 'block';\r\n                    })\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n```\r\nIt's frustrating when clicking in the search bar and reloading the first few times doesn't work, so I have some general questions:\r\n- What could be causing this delay, and if so what can be done about it?\r\n- Does a promise implementation for instantsearch.js make sense?\r\n\r\nThere are no slow network issues on my end.",
